 "components": {
  "instruction": "You are given a text describing a user's banking or payment-related scenario or question. Your task is to classify this text into one of the following specific categories, each representing a particular type of customer support request or issue:\n\n- automatic_top_up\n- balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer\n- beneficiary_not_allowed\n- cancel_transfer\n- card_payment_fee_charged\n- card_payment_not_recognised\n- declined_cash_withdrawal\n- exchange_rate\n- exchange_via_app\n- failed_transfer\n- get_disposable_virtual_card\n- get_physical_card\n- passcode_forgotten\n- pending_top_up\n- pending_transfer\n- receiving_money\n- reverted_card_payment?\n- top_up_by_cash_or_cheque\n- top_up_reverted\n- topping_up_by_card\n- transfer_fee_charged\n- transfer_into_account\n- transfer_timing\n- verify_my_identity\n- verify_source_of_funds\n\nInstructions:\n\n1. Carefully read the provided \"text\" input. This will usually be a short description or question from a user regarding a banking/payment functionality, transaction, or issue.\n2. Based on the text, select the most accurate and specific category from the above list. Only output one category.\n3. Pay close attention to the intent and specific vocabulary in the text. Ensure you understand subtle differences between categories:\n   - For questions about where transferred funds are or why a recent transfer isn’t showing, use 'balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer'.\n   - For issues asking about card/PIN delivery (e.g., PIN not arrived, where is my card), use 'get_physical_card'.\n   - Do not confuse requests about forgotten passcodes with requests about physical cards or delivery delays.\n   - 'transfer_into_account' is for general questions about transferring money into the account, NOT for missing or unconfirmed transfers.\n   - If the question is about setting up, receiving, or information regarding a specific feature (card, top-up, PIN, etc.), match it to the appropriate category.\n4. If an input describes an outcome or failed action (e.g., transfer failed, top-up pending), select the relevant status-related category.\n5. Use only the exact category label as your output, with no additional text.\n\nYour answer must accurately reflect the intended support issue described in the input according to these definitions and distinctions."
 },
